<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1882-05-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1882-05-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="298" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d298">
                        <head>No. 236.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Frelinghuysen</persName> to Señor <persName type="to">Romero</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1882-05-12"><hi rend="italic">May</hi> 12,
                                1882</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the pleasure to inclose for your
                            information a copy of a letter from the Secretary of War of the 8th
                            instant, in relation to the recent successful operations against the
                            hostile Apaches on the border.</p>
                        <p>Accept, &amp;c.,</p>
                        <closer><signed>FRED’K T. FRELINGHUYSEN.</signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>